text:
Yea.
It was a colossal feel bad. I’d been playing Commander for maybe 6-8 months with a small group. I activated an ability three times (announcing and holding priority for each). They cast Trickbind and claiming the other disappeared as well. I forget their exact wording but they claimed that because it prevented activation I could have the other triggers.
It was 2vs.1 against two more experienced players, and it left an immensely sour taste in my mouth.
What douchenozzles
Did you ever find out if they were malicious or just dumb?

Most likely dumb, but either way it sucked.
For context, we were all part of the same organization and they were “senior leadership” so it tacked onto that perception.

That group was awful as a whole, and I’m glad it’s mostly disbanded. I saw one of them at a wedding, and one of them told me “oh I see you wrote an article about my Savra deck, I could’ve sent you a decklist.”

To be fair, I based the article off my experience vs. him, but that didn’t come off well.
You could tell them to suck a fart too

Mini-rant over.
I have immensely negative feelings for that period of playing Magic, and I could keep going forever, so apologies for dragging that out more.
You're good
